---
// Simplified homepage — prose-first, one code example, one terminal proof.
---

<section class="home-content">

  <div class="value-props">
    <div class="prop">
      <strong>Arrow-native end to end.</strong>
      Data stays in columnar format from handler to wire. No JSON serialization, no encoding overhead.
    </div>
    <div class="prop">
      <strong>Two transports, one definition.</strong>
      The same Protocol serves subprocess stdin/stdout and HTTP. Switch with one line.
    </div>
    <div class="prop">
      <strong>Runtime introspection built in.</strong>
      Any vgi-rpc client discovers your methods, their schemas, and their docs automatically.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="code-section">
    <p class="code-label">A complete RPC server in 8 lines</p>
    <div class="code-block">
      <pre><code><span class="kw">const</span> protocol = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="cls">Protocol</span>(<span class="str">"Calculator"</span>);

protocol.<span class="fn">unary</span>(<span class="str">"add"</span>, {'{'}
  params: {'{'} a: <span class="typ">float</span>, b: <span class="typ">float</span> {'}'},
  result: {'{'} result: <span class="typ">float</span> {'}'},
  handler: <span class="kw">async</span> ({'{'} a, b {'}'}) =&gt; ({'{'} result: a + b {'}'}),
{'}'});

<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="cls">VgiRpcServer</span>(protocol).<span class="fn">run</span>();</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="terminal-section">
    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <span class="dot red"></span>
        <span class="dot yellow"></span>
        <span class="dot green"></span>
      </div>
      <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> vgi-rpc call add a=2 b=3
<span class="out">{'{'}result: 5.0{'}'}</span></code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

<style>
  .home-content {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1rem 3rem;
  }

  /* ── Value propositions ── */
  .value-props {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }
  .prop {
    font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .prop strong {
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
  }

  /* ── Code example ── */
  .code-section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .code-label {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .code-block {
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
    background: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
  }
  .code-block pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .code-block code {
    font-family: var(--__sl-font-mono);
    background: none;
  }

  /* ── Syntax colors (farm palette) ── */
  .kw { color: #c8a43a; }
  .cls { color: #6ba034; }
  .fn { color: #8bb85a; }
  .str { color: #d4b64e; }
  .typ { color: #6ba034; }

  /* ── Terminal proof ── */
  .terminal-section {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .terminal {
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
    background: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
    width: 22rem;
  }
  .terminal-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    background: var(--sl-color-gray-5);
  }
  .dot {
    width: 0.5rem;
    height: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .dot.red { background: #e5534b; }
  .dot.yellow { background: #c8a43a; }
  .dot.green { background: #4a7c23; }
  .terminal pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .terminal code {
    font-family: var(--__sl-font-mono);
    background: none;
  }
  .prompt { color: #4a7c23; font-weight: 700; }
  .out { color: var(--sl-color-gray-2); }
</style>
